OpenDGD — Licensing
===================

OpenDGD is published by NCB Hazcheck (a National Cargo Bureau company). It is
distributed under a dual licence so that the standard is free to read, cite and
implement, and the reference code is free to reuse.

1. Specification and normative artefacts — CC BY 4.0
----------------------------------------------------
The following are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International licence (CC BY 4.0), https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/ :

  - spec/SPEC.md
  - spec/opendgd.schema.json
  - spec/rendering.md
  - spec/openapi.yaml
  - the documentation under docs/

You are free to share and adapt these for any purpose, including commercially,
provided you give appropriate credit to "OpenDGD by NCB Hazcheck" and link to
https://opendgd.org.

2. Reference code, examples and conformance suite — Apache-2.0
-------------------------------------------------------------
All source code, the examples under examples/, and the conformance suite (when
published under spec/conformance/) are licensed under the Apache License,
Version 2.0, https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0 .

3. Trademarks
-------------
"OpenDGD", "NCB Hazcheck", "Hazcheck" and "National Cargo Bureau" and their
associated logos are marks of their respective owners. The licences above grant
no trademark rights. Do not imply endorsement or conformance without following
the process in GOVERNANCE.md.

